So my main problem with this is I don't think it would be classified at all. They wouldn't have given it a designation straight up just because of a potential connection to dado, which means it makes no sense to me for it to be Explained (because they never actually determined it was anomalous before hand.) Obviously the incidents with the billboards was anomalous, so I kind of feel like that should have been the actual target of the article rather than the laundry itself.

The other thing is just how free this agent is throwing around information to the random civilian that, for all they know, is working directly for (or could even BE) dado.

I won't downvote, because it's otherwise well written and did make me laugh in a few places, but I can't upvote it.







